@startuml
title Job Seeker - Sequence Diagram

autonumber

actor "Job Seeker" as User
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "Backend (NestJS)" as BE
database "MongoDB" as DB
participant "Notification Service" as NS

== Browse Jobs ==

User ->> FE: Open portal
FE ->> BE: Request available jobs
BE ->> DB: Fetch jobs and company data
DB -->> BE: Job list
BE -->> FE: Return job list
FE -->> User: Display jobs

== Search Jobs ==

User ->> FE: Search / Filter / Sort jobs
FE ->> BE: Send search criteria
BE ->> DB: Query matching jobs
DB -->> BE: Matching jobs
BE -->> FE: Return filtered jobs
FE -->> User: Show search results

== View Job ==

User ->> FE: View job details
FE ->> BE: Request job details
BE ->> DB: Fetch job information
DB -->> BE: Job details
BE -->> FE: Return job details
FE -->> User: Display job information

== Apply for Job ==

User ->> FE: Submit application & resume
FE ->> BE: Send application
BE ->> DB: Save application
DB -->> BE: Application saved

BE ->> NS: Send application confirmation
NS -->> User: Confirmation notification

BE -->> FE: Application submitted
FE -->> User: Show success message

== Save Job ==

User ->> FE: Save job
FE ->> BE: Save wishlist item
BE ->> DB: Store saved job
DB -->> BE: Saved successfully
BE -->> FE: Wishlist updated
FE -->> User: Saved confirmation

== Employer Updates Status ==

Note over BE,NS
Employer reviews the application,
updates status, or schedules an interview.
end note

BE ->> DB: Update application status
DB -->> BE: Status updated

BE ->> NS: Send status/interview notification
NS -->> User: Status update email/SSE notification

@enduml